statement.markdown:
Given a generic class `Container<T>` that can hold a value of type `T`, implement the `getvalue` method to return the stored value. However, the current implementation has a logical bug. The `Container` class is defined as follows:

```typescript
class Container<T> {
  private value: T;
  constructor(value: T) {
    this.value = value;
  }
  getvalue(): T {
    return this.value;
  }
}
```

Your task is to fix the bug in the `getvalue` method to ensure correct type inference for the returned value.

